Description
-----------

This extension takes screenshots of your current hangout and saves them to Google+ History.
Images will be uploaded to Google Drive and added to Google+ History from there.

Installation
------------

  * Sign-up for the Google+ History Developer Preview: https://developers.google.com/+/history/preview/

  * Go to https://code.google.com/apis/console/ and create a new project.

  * Activate the "Drive API", "Google+ API" and "Google+ History API" in Services.

  * The files server/oauth_callback.html and server/oauth_callback.html2 need to be uploaded to a publicly available website path (<YOUR_REDIRECT_PATH>).

  * Create a new Client ID for web application in API Access

  * Add <YOUR_REDIRECT_PATH>/oauth_callback.html and <YOUR_REDIRECT_PATH>/oauth_callback2.html as Redirect URIs

  * Edit extension/oauth2/adapters/google.js and extension/adapters/google2.js and replace <YOUR_REDIRECT_PATH> with your server path where you uploaded the files.

  * Edit extension/manifest.json and replace <YOUR_REDIRECT_PATH> there as well.

  * Edit moments_background.js and replace <CLIENT_ID> and <CLIENT_SECRET> with your information from the API Console.

  * Load the extension as unpacked extension in Google Chrome


